# Development Standards

## No Shortcuts Policy (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- NEVER use workarounds (wrong enums, skipped migrations, hardcoded values, mock data)
- ALWAYS use proper migrations, correct enums, Mojaloop/ISO 20022 standards
- NEVER hardcode credentials, amounts, or IDs — use environment variables and DB
- Real transactions only — no dummy data in any environment
- See `docs/ZERO_SHORTCUTS_POLICY.md` for full policy

## Definition of Done (EVERY task must have ALL of these)

1. ✅ Clean code with zero linter errors
2. ✅ Documentation updated in `docs/`
3. ✅ Tests authored (unit/integration) with run instructions
4. ✅ Migrations written with rollbacks
5. ✅ Security review completed
6. ✅ Changes committed and pushed
7. ✅ Session log created
8. ✅ Agent handover updated

## Security Requirements (Banking-Grade — NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- Input validation and sanitization at every API boundary
- JWT HS512 with short expiry
- Parameterized queries only — no string interpolation in SQL
- AES-256-GCM encryption for sensitive data
- TLS 1.3 enforced
- RBAC access control
- Structured logging with PII redaction (no phone numbers, names, or IDs in logs)
- Mojaloop FSPIOP standards
- ISO 27001 ready
- POPIA compliance (no personal data caching)

## Error Handling

- Structured error responses with consistent format and HTTP status codes
- Safe user messaging — never expose internal errors, stack traces, or DB details
- Transaction rollback on error — ACID compliance
- Validate all inputs at API boundary

## Frontend Standards

- Codebase is source of truth for frontend — agents may edit any UI/frontend files
- Global design system: CSS variables, Montserrat font, brand green accents, white headers
- Mobile-first, responsive design
- All new overlays/pages must have: TopBanner, scrollable body, sticky BottomNavigation
- Add new paths to `pagesWithTopBanner` in `App.tsx` and both allowlists in `BottomNavigation.tsx`

## Scripts — Sweep First

**Always** run `ls scripts/` before creating any new script. Over 200 scripts exist. Creating duplicates wastes context and causes confusion.

## Working Directory

- ONLY work in `/mymoolah/` and subdirectories
- Settings changes: `/portal/` directories only
- Never use git worktrees
